text: The slendertail moray eel (Gymnothorax gracilicauda) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific Ocean.Gymnothorax gracilicauda at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Jenkins in 1903, and is also commonly known as the graceful-tailed moray.Gymnothorax gracilicauda at www.fishbase.org. ==References== gracilicauda Category:Fish described in 1903 Category:Taxa named by Oliver Peebles Jenkins]
title: Slendertail moray eel
